=== Etymology ===
Middle English [[mayde]], [[maide]], from Old English [[mægð]], [[mægden]], from common Germanic ''*magadi(n)'', derived from Proto-Indo-European ''*magh(u)-'' "young person".  Near cognates include Dutch [[maagd]], German [[Magd]], and Gothic [[������]] (magaþs).  

